Nick Di Vona interview.
Nick Di Vona is a developer who got #2 in the AppStore with his IOS app PokeRadar which has about 2Million active users at the moment and has been sold to the famous Company Glu (The makers of "Deer Hunter" game and others) for 500K $ !!!!!!! 
He talks about what he did and the story behind his outstanding success.
The interview could be watched by anyone but it's mobile development oriented but watch it anyway he gives general information and advices.

Linked Data

Linked Data is one of the core concepts and pillars of the Semantic Web, also known as the Web of Data. The Semantic Web is all about making links between datasets understandable not only to humans but also to machines, and Linked Data provides the best practices for making those links. Linked Data is a set of design principles for sharing machine-readable interlinked data on the Web.
